HEADWORD: Serosity
<hw>Se*ros"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>serosit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See <er>Serous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The quality or state of being serous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A thin watery animal fluid, as
synovial fluid and pericardial fluid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Serotherapy</ent>⟦br⟧
